---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import EquationCanon from '../components/EquationCanon.astro';
---

<Base
  title="About — Yeqiu He"
  description="Yeqiu He: theoretical physics background, AI systems engineer, writer of long-form science history."
  lang="en"
  altHref="/zh/about/"
>
  <main class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-6 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-chalk">About</h1>
    <div class="mt-8 space-y-5 leading-relaxed text-ink">
      <p>
        I'm <strong class="text-chalk">Yeqiu He</strong> (贺冶秋) — trained in theoretical physics,
        working as an <strong class="text-chalk">AI systems engineer</strong>. I build agent systems
        with real memory architectures, retrieval pipelines that treat grounding as an engineering
        problem, and the occasional game engine for fun.
      </p>
      <p>
        The physics never left. It shows up as an obsession with <em>why things are true</em>:
        my <a class="text-accent-soft underline underline-offset-2" href="/writing/">long-form essays</a>
        walk through group theory, the Monster, and Euler's life at whiteboard depth — and the
        <a class="text-accent-soft underline underline-offset-2" href="/projects/">systems I build</a>
        carry the same habit, from Monte-Carlo equity engines to review chains that catch fabricated evidence.
      </p>
      <p>
        Currently based in Germany, relocating to Australia. I run an
        <a class="text-accent-soft underline underline-offset-2" href="/projects/openclaw-fleet/">eight-agent fleet</a>
        that helps research, build, and review — this site included.
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>
  <EquationCanon lang="en" />
</Base>
